          "updatedAt": "2024-09-04T14:27:29Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "becarpenter",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "body": "The word \"adopt\" does not occur anywhere in this section, yet it is a _de facto_ part of WG process. I suggest that we should add a very brief definition of adoption something like:\n\nWorking Groups MAY formally adopt an Internet-Draft to indicate that it is being considered as a candidate for publication as an RFC.\n\n(Anything beyond that can be in a separate document; this is just an anchor.)",
          "createdAt": "2025-08-29T07:44:07Z",
          "updatedAt": "2025-08-29T07:44:07Z"
        }
