      "body": "From Brian E Carpenter on the mailing list:\n\n> Adoption is _not_ a formal step in the IETF process described by RFC 2026\n> and RFC 2418. Most newcomers seem to assume that it is, since it's\n> entrenched in common practice and in the tracker.\n\n> There is a question that the WG charter allows us to ask: should WG\n> adoption be mentioned in section 8.2 of 2418bis? That is distinct from\n> the longer term question of pursuing draft-carpenter-gendispatch-rfc7221bis.",
