    {
      "number": 27,
      "id": "I_kwDOMaVM687QJQ3o",
      "title": "do virtual side meetings count as BOFs",
      "url": "https://github.com/ietf-wg-procon/2418bis/issues/27",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "mcr",
      "authorAssociation": "NONE",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [
        "discuss"
      ],
      "body": "I think some clarification would be useful as to whether virtual interim (side)meetings count as BOFs.\n\n2418 speaks about 1 BOF, with 2 being an exception.\n2 BOFs is now very common, with one or more side meetings even occuring.\nBOF organizers/proponents often (particularly pandemic) have weekly to monthly organizing meetings.\nThis is done using ad-hoc meeting technology, which often results in problems accessing for some, lack of good records.  Many would prefer to use meetecho for this, but then there was push back that said if it used the official tool, then it would be a BOF.\nIf the reason to limit BOFs to <= 2 is due to time constraints for plenary week, then any time elsewhere (elsewhen?) should not count.\nIf there are other reasons to limit BOF, then they should be enumerated.\n\nThere is also now an IAB involvement in bringing new work.\n\nreplacing ietf-wg-procon/2026bis#19, and this issue should move to other repo.\n",
      "createdAt": "2025-08-29T00:42:21Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-10-07T16:01:17Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    }
