      "number": 26,
      "id": "PR_kwDOMaVM686sYSmr",
      "title": "Make milestones optional",
      "url": "https://github.com/ietf-wg-procon/2418bis/pull/26",
      "state": "MERGED",
      "author": "DavidSchinazi",
      "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "This PR incorporates draft-schinazi-update-on-milestones into draft-ietf-procon-2418bis. It makes changes to all mentions of milestones in the document.",
      "createdAt": "2025-10-06T22:00:43Z",
      "updatedAt": "2025-10-15T17:50:37Z",
      "baseRepository": "ietf-wg-procon/2418bis",
      "baseRefName": "main",
      "baseRefOid": "2be7a565ca16cf83428de6b31391ccb0b2da9c68",
      "headRepository": "ietf-wg-procon/2418bis",
      "headRefName": "milestones",
      "headRefOid": "ec6dc4fe92171ce683712c3420eb7c6209bf64d6",
      "closedAt": "2025-10-15T17:50:36Z",
      "mergedAt": "2025-10-15T17:50:36Z",
      "mergedBy": "richsalz",
      "mergeCommit": {
        "oid": "7b6aff31d4beefd0504e0386a1b49e8dabfe604a"
      },
      "comments": [
        {
          "author": "becarpenter",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "body": "It seems very restrictive that the decision whether or not to specify milestones is made once and for all when a WG is first chartered. It would be quite plausible for a WG with or without milestones to change mode as its role evolves. I suggest that it should be \"when a WG is first chartered _or rechartered_\".",
          "createdAt": "2025-10-08T01:51:52Z",
          "updatedAt": "2025-10-08T01:51:52Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "DavidSchinazi",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "body": "Hi @becarpenter, I agree with you. This is already the case though - does the following sentence not cover it for you?\r\n\r\n> Similarly, the Area Director can enable or disable milestones, or enable or disable dates, or change the granularity of dates, all without a formal recharter.",
          "createdAt": "2025-10-08T03:01:07Z",
          "updatedAt": "2025-10-08T03:01:07Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "becarpenter",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "body": "Yes, I guess, but the present text could be read as setting the decision in concrete.",
          "createdAt": "2025-10-08T03:27:27Z",
          "updatedAt": "2025-10-08T03:27:27Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "DavidSchinazi",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "body": "That's totally fair, and I'm happy to improve it. Do you have a suggestion for how to make it sound less final without repeating the other section too much?",
          "createdAt": "2025-10-08T03:46:41Z",
          "updatedAt": "2025-10-08T03:46:41Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "becarpenter",
          "authorAssociation": "NONE",
          "body": "You know, one word would do it:\r\n\r\n> While chartering a new working group, the IESG will decide whether\r\n> milestones are _initially_  enabled or disabled for this working group,",
          "createdAt": "2025-10-08T04:37:44Z",
          "updatedAt": "2025-10-08T04:37:44Z"
        },
        {
          "author": "DavidSchinazi",
          "authorAssociation": "COLLABORATOR",
          "body": "I like that. Added the word \"initially\". Thanks for the suggestion.",
          "createdAt": "2025-10-08T18:51:00Z",
          "updatedAt": "2025-10-08T18:51:00Z"
        }
      ],
      "reviews": [
        {
